HEADWORD: Sheepback
<hw>Sheep"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A rounded knoll of rock resembling the back of a sheep. -- produced
by glacial action. Called also <altname>roche
moutonn⟦eacute⟧e</altname>; -- usually in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

